OOP -> Object Oriented Programming

Features of OOP:
1)object : Any Entity which has own state and behaviour that is called an object


ex: pen,paper etc..

2)class: Collection of objects that is called class 
ex: human body

3)abstraction: Hiding internal details and showing functionalities that is called abstraction
ex:fb login page

4)Encapsualtion: Wrapping up of data or binding of data that is called encapsualtion
ex:capsule

5)Inheritance: When one object acquire all the properties and behaviour of parent class
ex:father-son

6)Polymorphism: Many ways to perform anything
ex: Many ways 
